    "notes": "Carvana listing (vehicle #4357083, stock 2004739381) — fully online, FREE nationwide shipping, next-day available. $34,590 after a $400 price drop (was $34,990); no-haggle, no dealer doc fees — only CA tax + registration on top. Buyer protection: 7-day money-back return + Carvana's 100-day/4,189-mi limited warranty (CarvanaCare available). VIN 4T3B6RFV8PU120326 (the 'P' = 2023). Silver Sky Metallic / Black SofTex. Only 1 key included — budget ~$300–400 for a spare smart key.\n\nPRIOR USE: LEASE — a lease return, NOT a rental/fleet car. A lease return is essentially a one-driver personal-use car with a contract mileage cap and maintenance kept up to avoid lease-end penalties; the on-paper 'owner' is just the leasing bank (Toyota Financial). Much closer to personal use than to fleet — only a mild caveat. The low 37.8k miles is exactly the lease-cap profile.\n\n*** ACCIDENT REPORTED — Carvana's inspection summary shows History = \"Accident reported\" (under-hood, exterior, interior, drive, looks, detailing all Passed). Severity/repair quality is NOT given — PULL THE FREE CARFAX before going further to learn if it was minor cosmetic or structural/airbag. This is the key change from my first pass (I had accidents as unknown; now confirmed ≥1). Disclosed cosmetic wear (Condition x4): etched hood, chip on rear driver door, trim wear on rear bumper, worn/faded front driver seat — minor, and part of why it's priced low.\n\nFundamentals still strong: LOWEST miles on the board (37,802 ≈ 12.6k/yr), ~22k mi factory powertrain warranty left (≈2028), fully-loaded XLE Premium. Equipment CONFIRMED both ways (Carvana lists features in full): HAS moonroof, power liftgate, power driver seat + lumbar, SofTex seats, full safety suite (adaptive cruise, lane-keep, AEB, blind-spot, rear cross-traffic, pedestrian detection, backup cam), heated mirrors, alloys, roof rails, LED lights. DOES NOT HAVE heated front seats, heated steering wheel, or JBL (no Weather Package).\n\nRevised standing: it NO LONGER cleanly dominates c8/c9 the way it looked at first — both of those have CLEAN, 0-accident histories, while this now carries a reported accident + cosmetic wear + is a lease return. c10 still wins on miles/price/equipment; c8 and c9 win on history. For your priorities, c4 (2023 SE — heated seats + wheel + moonroof confirmed, clean, 0 accidents) is the better fit unless you specifically want c10's lower miles and accept the accident.\n\nExpert 3/5 (was 4 before the accident disclosure): excellent miles/price/equipment for the money, but a reported accident + cosmetic blemishes + lease return + single key pull it back to a 3. Could nudge to ~3.5 if the CARFAX shows a minor, well-repaired cosmetic hit — or lower if it was structural/airbag. Re-rate after you read the accident detail.",
