    "notes": "Capitol Toyota (DGDG group, San Jose ~25 mi; stock 113635R). The FIRST XSE on your board — the sporty trim that slots between XLE Premium and the Limited: XLE-Premium comfort kit + sport-tuned suspension + black exterior accents + the signature two-tone paint (Silver Sky body, Midnight Black roof). Optioned with the XSE Advanced Technology Package (12.3\" digital cluster, Bird's Eye View 360 camera, front/rear parking assist w/ auto-braking, Qi charging) and the XSE Weather Package (heated seats + heated steering wheel).\n\nFIT — very strong: it confirms every priority comfort you track — panoramic glass roof + power moonroof + heated front seats + heated steering wheel + power liftgate + 8-way power driver seat are ALL present (9/10 tracked features). The one miss: NO JBL — this car's window sticker lists a 6-speaker system, not the 11-speaker JBL. (Correction from my first pass: the panoramic glass roof is NOT Limited-only — it's part of the XSE Advanced Technology Package this car carries; I'd misread the sticker's base-trim '1st-row sliding sunroof' boilerplate as a plain moonroof.) So on tracked features it's as loaded as the c13 Limited except JBL and ventilated seats. (Open question: the same Advanced Tech Package on the near-twin c15 includes a JBL premium system — if c14 actually has JBL too, it's a 10/10; its sticker said 6 speakers, so confirm the audio at the dealer.)\n\nPRICE / VALUE: $36,990. CARFAX History-Based Value is ~$37,250, so it's listed $260 BELOW CARFAX value and badged 'Good Value' + 'Great Reliability' — fair, not a steal. Est. fees ~$122 (DGDG's $85 doc + ~$37 e-file, same as the c13 sister store) + CA tax/reg.\n\nHISTORY: CARFAX 1-owner, clean title, NO accidents/damage. Prior use = PERSONAL LEASE (a lease return — one driver, leasing bank on title, NOT a rental/fleet car), registered in Southern California (Whittier → Woodland Hills → Thousand Oaks), then wholesaled up to San Jose. A lease return is close to personal use — only a mild caveat.\n\n*** THREE things to weigh: (1) ~16.7k mi/yr (CARFAX estimate; the card's model-year math shows ~16.3k) — above the ~12k average (the amber flag). That's high even for a lease (caps are usually 10–15k/yr), so the lessee likely paid mileage overage — fine mechanically on a Toyota hybrid, but reflect the extra wear + shorter remaining warranty in your offer. (2) THIN service history — CARFAX shows only 2 service records, and the first substantive one isn't until 45,731 mi (01/10/2026, Thousand Oaks Toyota): a big bundled job incl. oil/filter, 4-wheel alignment, fuel-system clean, AIR FILTER + MASS-AIRFLOW-SENSOR replacement. A ~46k-mi gap to the first recorded service, then a heavy service right before the lease-return sale, reads like pre-sale reconditioning — ask why the MAF sensor was replaced (warranty? a running issue?) and whether earlier oil changes were done off-record. (3) WARRANTY nearly out by miles — powertrain 5yr/60k is active by date (≈2028) but only ~11k mi remain; at this rate it's effectively gone by ~mid-2027. The valuable hybrid coverage (system 8yr/100k ≈2031, battery 10yr/150k ≈2033) stays intact. Not Toyota CPO. Also: it's been listed ~12 weeks (online 03/20, at Capitol since 04/02/2026) → stale-listing negotiation leverage.\n\nHOW IT STACKS UP: vs c13 (2023 Limited, $40,499, 30k mi, personal) — c13 adds JBL + ventilated seats + a digital rearview mirror and is lower-miles + personal-not-lease, but ~$3.5k more (c14 now matches it on the panoramic roof). vs c4 (2023 SE, Redwood City, $34,641, 45.7k mi, personal) — c4 is ~$2.3k cheaper, slightly fewer miles, personal-use, and closer (12 mi), and also has heated seats/wheel/moonroof; this XSE adds the confirmed power seat, two-tone styling, the 360 camera + 12.3\" display + Qi. vs c12 (2024 SE, Fremont, $34,998, 47.8k mi, 19 service records) — c12 is newer with far better-documented maintenance but has NO moonroof; this XSE adds the moonroof and more tech for ~$2k more.\n\nExpert 4/5: one of the best comfort-FIT cars on the board — it confirms the panoramic roof + moonroof + heated seats + heated wheel + power liftgate + power seat you keep chasing, in the sporty XSE trim with the nicest tech short of the Limited, fairly priced (below CARFAX value), clean 1-owner no-accident history, and local-ish. Held back from 5 by the above-average ~16.7k mi/yr, the thin 2-record service history with that pre-sale recon service to explain, a powertrain warranty nearly used up by miles, no JBL (6-speaker audio), and no CPO. Drive it, ask about the MAF-sensor replacement + missing early service, and use the ~12-week listing age to push under $36k. Re-rate after you see it.",
