    "notes": "CarMax (stock 28733487), at CarMax Vancouver, WA. *** STATUS: currently ON HOLD / RESERVED for another buyer — CarMax shows 'On hold for someone' and only a 'Notify Me' button, so you CAN'T buy it right now. It may free up if that buyer's hold lapses; set a CarMax 'Notify Me' alert and treat this as a watch-item, not an actionable buy. (I surfaced 'ON HOLD' in the card's location line.)\n\nTHE OTHER catch — PRICE: $41,998 + $299 ship = ~$42,297 all-in is the MOST EXPENSIVE car on your entire board — ~$5k over the other XSEs (c14 $36,990, c15 $35,995, c16 $37,998), above the c13 Limited ($40,499), and at/above this XSE's ORIGINAL loaded MSRP (~$41k). Paying near-new money for a used 30k-mile car is poor value, even for the newest one. CarMax is no-haggle, so the only realistic path is to wait for a price drop (they cut these 'to match market').\n\nWHY IT'S STILL TEMPTING — the best CAR of the XSEs on fundamentals: it's the NEWEST (a 2024), with the LOWEST miles (29,683 ≈ ~14–15k/yr), and the ONLY one with FACTORY BASIC bumper-to-bumper warranty STILL ACTIVE (in service 05/2024 → ~1 yr/~6k mi of basic left), plus the most powertrain buffer (~30k mi). Fully loaded 10/10 — JBL, Panoramic Sunroof, heated seats + wheel (Cold Weather Pkg), memory/power seats, power hatch, even a Tow Hitch. AutoCheck = SINGLE owner, Vehicle Usage = PERSONAL, clean title, NO accidents, 7 service records (dealer-serviced in Oregon: 25k service done), AutoCheck Buyback-Protection eligible. Only 1 open recall (25TA08 meter — free fix), vs c16's 2.\n\nHISTORY: Oregon car — in service 05/2024, one personal owner in Portland/OR, steady ~14–15k mi/yr, now at CarMax Vancouver WA (just across the river). Clean throughout; lien reported (normal, financed).\n\nExpert 3/5: the car itself is a 4 — newest, lowest-miles, best-warranty, fully-loaded, clean personal 1-owner — but I'm docking it for being the PRICIEST vehicle on your board (at/above original MSRP, ~$5k over the other XSEs and over budget) AND currently ON HOLD/unavailable. Net: set a Notify alert and watch it, but at $41,998 it's a weak value vs c15 (clean, equally-loaded 10/10, $35,995). Only worth chasing if it frees up AND the price falls meaningfully — though if you specifically want the newest year + active basic warranty + lowest miles, this is the one to watch.",
